<div class="container mt-4">
  <h1>Help & Documentation</h1>

  <div class="row mt-4">
    <div class="col-lg-8">
      <!-- Overview -->
      <section class="mb-5">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          Codeplug App helps you manage radio programming data (codeplugs) in a universal format,
          then export it to CSV files compatible with different radio programming software.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Getting Started -->
      <section class="mb-5">
        <h2>Getting Started</h2>
        <ol class="list-group list-group-numbered">
          <li class="list-group-item">
            <strong>Create an Account:</strong> Sign up with your email address and callsign
          </li>
          <li class="list-group-item">
            <strong>Browse Radio Models:</strong> View supported radio models and their specifications
          </li>
          <li class="list-group-item">
            <strong>Create Your Codeplug:</strong> Define channels, zones, and systems
          </li>
          <li class="list-group-item">
            <strong>Export:</strong> Generate CSV files for your specific radio model
          </li>
          <li class="list-group-item">
            <strong>Program Your Radio:</strong> Import the CSV into your radio's programming software
          </li>
        </ol>
      </section>

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <section class="mb-5">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="accordion" id="faqAccordion">
          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
              <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq1">
                What is a codeplug?
              </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="faq1" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
              <div class="accordion-body">
                A codeplug is the complete programming configuration for a two-way radio, including channels,
                zones, talkgroups, and system settings. Different radio manufacturers use different formats
                and terminology, but Codeplug App provides a universal way to manage this data.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
              <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq2">
                What radio models are supported?
              </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="faq2" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
              <div class="accordion-body">
                We support dozens of radio models from manufacturers including Motorola, Baofeng, Anytone,
                TYT, Kenwood, Icom, Yaesu, and more. You can browse the full list of supported models in the
                Radio Models section. Users can also create custom export layouts for unsupported radios.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
              <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq3">
                What modes are supported?
              </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="faq3" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
              <div class="accordion-body">
                Codeplug App supports analog FM, DMR (Digital Mobile Radio), P25 (Project 25), and NXDN modes.
                Each mode has specific settings like CTCSS/DCS tones for analog, color codes for DMR, and NAC for P25.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
              <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq4">
                How do zones work?
              </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="faq4" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
              <div class="accordion-body">
                Zones are logical groupings of channels. In Codeplug App, zones can contain unlimited channels.
                When exporting to a specific radio, if your zone exceeds the radio's capacity, the app will
                help you split it into multiple zones that fit your radio's limitations.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
              <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#faq5">
                Can I share my codeplugs?
              </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="faq5" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#faqAccordion">
              <div class="accordion-body">
                Yes! Codeplugs can be marked as public or private. Public codeplugs can be discovered and used
                by other users in your area, making it easy to share repeater and talkgroup configurations with
                your local ham radio community.
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Key Concepts -->
      <section class="mb-5">
        <h2>Key Concepts</h2>

        <h4 class="mt-3">Channels</h4>
        <p>
          A channel is your complete configuration for accessing a specific system (repeater or simplex frequency).
          It includes frequency, mode, power level, bandwidth, and mode-specific settings.
        </p>

        <h4 class="mt-3">Systems</h4>
        <p>
          A system represents a repeater or simplex frequency with its technical specifications. Systems are
          shared across the community, so you can reference existing repeater configurations.
        </p>

        <h4 class="mt-3">Talkgroups</h4>
        <p>
          For digital modes (DMR, P25), talkgroups organize conversations by topic or region. The app maintains
          a database of talkgroups organized by networks like Brandmeister, TGIF, and regional systems.
        </p>

        <h4 class="mt-3">Radio Models</h4>
        <p>
          Each radio model has specific capabilities and limitations (maximum zones, channels per zone, name lengths,
          supported modes). The app uses these specifications to ensure your exports are compatible.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Need More Help -->
      <section class="mb-5">
        <div class="alert alert-info">
          <h5>Need More Help?</h5>
          <p class="mb-0">
            If you have questions not answered here, please visit our
            <a href="https://github.com/livitup/codeplug_app/discussions" class="alert-link" target="_blank">GitHub Discussions</a>
            or report an issue on our
            <a href="https://github.com/livitup/codeplug_app/issues" class="alert-link" target="_blank">GitHub Issues</a> page.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>

    <!-- Sidebar -->
    <div class="col-lg-4">
      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Quick Links</h5>
          <ul class="list-unstyled">
            <% if logged_in? %>
              <li class="mb-2"><%= link_to "Radio Models", radio_models_path %></li>
              <li class="mb-2"><%= link_to "My Profile", user_path(current_user) %></li>
            <% else %>
              <li class="mb-2"><%= link_to "Sign Up", new_user_path %></li>
              <li class="mb-2"><%= link_to "Log In", login_path %></li>
            <% end %>
            <li class="mb-2"><%= link_to "About", about_path %></li>
            <li class="mb-2"><%= link_to "Home", root_path %></li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
